00:44:01.019 --> 00:44:06.509
So that’s the Lakshmi Day when we say that
Lakshmi Puja takes place because that is the

00:44:06.509 --> 00:44:15.219
day you invite the Lakshmi to come in, the
Rajalakshmi, the Lakshmi by which you become

00:44:15.219 --> 00:44:27.499
the king of the family, or the royal benevolence
you can call it, the regal feeling in the

00:44:27.499 --> 00:44:34.829
family – that is the day.

00:44:34.829 --> 00:44:42.009
Then comes the day, next to that is the first
of the month in…

00:44:42.009 --> 00:44:48.109
That is the calendar, My forefathers, because
you’re all My children you have to use the

00:44:48.109 --> 00:44:53.309
same calendar, Shalivahanas calendar and that
is the first day of the Shalivahanas calendar.

00:44:53.309 --> 00:44:57.140
And what do they do in the morning time to
celebrate it?

00:44:57.140 --> 00:45:09.699
They take one of these jars, Aquarius and
put a shawl with it and that is put as a flag,

00:45:09.699 --> 00:45:13.289
representing the Aquarius and the shawl of
the Mother.

00:45:13.289 --> 00:45:17.650
That’s why they are called as Shalivahana
– the ones who carry the shawls of the Mother,

00:45:17.650 --> 00:45:20.400
the “carriers of the shawls of the Mother”.

00:45:20.400 --> 00:45:23.910
That’s how they put it up.

00:45:23.910 --> 00:45:28.119
The shawl on top of the Aquarius.

00:45:28.119 --> 00:45:38.509
This should be actually the flag of the Sahaja
Yogis that you make it the Aquarius or we

00:45:38.509 --> 00:45:49.199
can say the jar [- what do you call that pitcher?

00:45:49.199 --> 00:45:55.509
Or not pitcher but this lota business what
do you call that – there’s nothing used

00:45:55.509 --> 00:45:56.509
like that here.

00:45:56.509 --> 00:46:03.279
That one is kumbha – we can call in kumbha
and the shawl is there so they put it up.

00:46:03.279 --> 00:46:04.390
That’s why they] (FV note: The section between
square brackets was not found on either my

00:46:04.390 --> 00:46:05.390
audio tape or mp3 file, and hence could not
be verified.

00:46:05.390 --> 00:46:10.150
) call as Gudi Padwa, Padwa means first day
of the moon is Padwa, and Gudi means “this”.

00:46:10.150 --> 00:46:20.839
So they put it up and that is how they say
that today is the New Year day for the Shalivahanas.

00:46:20.839 --> 00:46:34.239
Shawl is the covering of your Mother which
gives it warmth and also it covers Her modesty.

00:46:34.239 --> 00:46:41.450
Shawl is a sign of regality and modesty and
chastity.

00:46:41.450 --> 00:46:42.979
So you stand for that of your Mother.

00:46:42.979 --> 00:46:53.400
You protect it like Ganesha does.

00:46:53.400 --> 00:47:00.130
Only on one point He gets angry, if anybody
says or does anything against the Mother,

00:47:00.130 --> 00:47:03.529
then He comes down.

00:47:03.529 --> 00:47:09.449
That’s why Christ has said: “Anything
against Me I’ll tolerate, but anything against

00:47:09.449 --> 00:47:14.299
the Holy Ghost, will not be forgiven.

00:47:14.299 --> 00:47:22.180
” That’s the Son talking about the Mother,
that’s what happens.

00:47:22.180 --> 00:47:25.589
So today is the second day.

00:47:25.589 --> 00:47:38.269
Second day is the Bija – is the they call
it the Bhav-bija is the day when the brother

00:47:38.269 --> 00:47:49.299
and the sister, who are the seeds of one tree
have that pure exchange of affection.

00:47:49.299 --> 00:47:55.209
The sister does the aarti of the brother,
gives him a tika and then brother gives her

00:47:55.209 --> 00:47:59.150
something as a token of his love, as a present.

00:47:59.150 --> 00:48:04.410
In Bombay we started that and they have made
sisters and brothers.

00:48:04.410 --> 00:48:08.299
I wish you also could find out somebody as
a nice brother.

00:48:08.299 --> 00:48:19.199
But I found that these relationships have
been so beautifully managed in India that

00:48:19.199 --> 00:48:27.999
if they could be managed here, it will be
a great day of really ecstasy for Me, because

00:48:27.999 --> 00:48:34.170
that means you have overcome this devil of
immorality.

00:48:34.170 --> 00:48:42.499
The purity, removing the lust and greed from
your mind completely and bestowing that affection

00:48:42.499 --> 00:48:47.170
for someone who is your sister.

00:48:47.170 --> 00:48:51.910
Very common in India, everybody has a sister
there; all the Sahaja Yogis have a sister

00:48:51.910 --> 00:48:55.509
and they look after their sister that way.

00:48:55.509 --> 00:49:02.969
Is a very sweet feeling and a sister is treated
– like Raulbai is a sister of Dumas you

00:49:02.969 --> 00:49:10.430
can imagine, and her sister is treated with
the same grace as the own sister is to be

00:49:10.430 --> 00:49:13.880
treated with all the relationships and everything.

00:49:13.880 --> 00:49:17.189
So this is the fifth day is Dwija.

00:49:17.189 --> 00:49:22.410
So from thirteenth to the fifth day they celebrate
Diwali.

00:49:22.410 --> 00:49:25.779
For us Diwali has a very great significance.

00:49:25.779 --> 00:49:35.400
That is, from one light many lights are awakened
and they are put in a line, so they are called

00:49:35.400 --> 00:49:39.309
as Diwali – means ‘the lights put in a
line’.

00:49:39.309 --> 00:49:47.650
So when you hold My Hands together all of
us – through that the energy passes and

00:49:47.650 --> 00:50:02.019
the enlightened rasa is established, and the
whole world has to become that beautiful reign

00:50:02.019 --> 00:50:18.059
of your Mother where nothing but the bliss
of your Father and His enjoyment when He sees

00:50:18.059 --> 00:50:24.569
His Own Creation dancing in that Ocean of
Bliss.

00:50:24.569 --> 00:50:26.720
May God bless you.
